                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d73">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1110: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Hankow</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Hankow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-25T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 25, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received April 25—5:40
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. My 25, April 23, 4 p.m. The following telegram has been sent to the
                    Legation.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“April 25, 11 a.m. My April 23, 3 p.m. I received this morning a personal
                        note from General Ho Ying-chin of which the following is the substance: The
                        communist brigands will be promptly exterminated; at present Kanchow is very
                        safe and quiet and no danger will arise; General Chin Han-ting has been
                        telegraphed to render protection to American life and property; hope is
                        expressed that I will entertain no anxiety for Kanchow.</p>
                    <p>While I have no means of knowing the basis of General Ho’s optimism, he is
                        generally well informed.</p>
                    <p>Repeated to Canton and the Department.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
